title: 2879 no power on
message:
Owners daughter inserted a 3.5mm charger in the headphone port with the other end connected to a usb port. 
Computer died!
It has green light, pp3v42_g3h and ppbus_g3h. 
What do i check?

title: 2879 no power on
message: Diode mode on L7260?, could be a dead Q4690....  Also remember, you should use power pads or keyboard to power on this board....

title: 2879 no power on
message:
L7260 is 0.450 in diode mode, same as other boards. 
Pin 5 and 8 on Q4690 have 3,3 volt. Same as working board.

title: 2879 no power on
message: Resistance to ground on pp3v42_g3h is 0.993 k. I think that is to low.

title: 2879 no power on
message: That is way too low, usually dead MCP.

title: 2879 no power on
message: Anything else on 3V42 rail, but lets be real it is always the MCP with these.
